cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.EM, cs.AR, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category as it deals with brain-like computing and associative learning. It could also belong to the Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) category as it involves the use of nanoscale memory devices. The paper also involves Electronic Materials (cs.EM) as it deals with phase change memory cells. Additionally, it could belong to the Augmented Reality (cs.AR) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) categories as it involves the organization of the biological brain and pattern recognition.
